<HL>
   Corning to Post Gain
</HL>
<DATE>
07/20/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B4
</SO>
<CO>
   GLW J.AHG
</CO>
<LP>
   CORNING, N.Y. -- Corning Inc. said it would post a
one-time, $18 million after-tax gain in the third quarter on
the sale of most of its 33% interest in a Japanese glass
company.
   Corning earned $75.9 million in the year-ago quarter.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Corning said the sale of its investment in Iwaki Glass Co.
of Japan to Asahi Glass Co. would release funds for new
investments.
   Corning is a telecommunications, specialty glass, ceramic
products and laboratory services concern.
</TEXT>
